  "notes": "Standard Italian (based on Florentine/Tuscan). Open/close mid-vowel distinction (e/ɛ, o/ɔ) is lexically determined and varies by region. Gemination is phonemic (fato/fatto). Gorgia toscana (intervocalic stop aspiration) is a regional Tuscan feature, not standard.",
